CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June, 7, 1941, pg. 4, reads: "Crown May Queen at Civic League's Dance - The varied activities of Pittsburgh's Junior Civic League extends to the crowning of a May Queen as was shown last week when Frankie Sims received that title at an elaborate coronation dance at the Moose Temple.  The front row above from left to right shows Anna Howard, Essie Mae Howard, Esther S. Atlen, Genevieve Rumble, Mimry Glass, and Annie P. Howard.  The second row shows Jean Gilbam, Frankie Sims, May Queen; Alice Morris, and Janie Miller. - Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Young women at Junior Civic League dance, front row: Anna Howard, Essie Mae Howard, Esther S. Atlen, Genevieve Rumble, Mimry Glass, Annie P. Howard; second row: Jean Gilbam, May Queen Frankie Sims, Alice Morris, and Janie Miller, in Moose Temple
